---
description: External service integration patterns and standards
alwaysApply: false
globs: mavaia_core/services/**/*.py
---

# Cursor Rules: Service Integration Standards

rules:
  - id: service_integration.patterns.interface_abstraction
    description: |
      External service integrations must use interface abstractions.
      - Define clear interfaces for external service interactions
      - Use dependency injection for service dependencies
      - Support multiple service implementations (e.g., different providers)
      - Document service interfaces and contracts
      - Test service integrations with mocks and stubs
    severity: error

  - id: service_integration.patterns.error_handling
    description: |
      Service integration errors must be handled gracefully.
      - Catch and handle service-specific exceptions
      - Provide meaningful error messages for service failures
      - Log service errors with appropriate context
      - Return structured error responses (success, error, error_code)
      - Implement fallback mechanisms when appropriate
    severity: error

  - id: service_integration.patterns.retry_logic
    description: |
      Retry logic must be implemented for transient service failures.
      - Use exponential backoff for retries
      - Set maximum retry attempts
      - Distinguish between retryable and non-retryable errors
      - Log retry attempts and outcomes
      - Document retry policies and behavior
    severity: error

  - id: service_integration.patterns.timeouts
    description: |
      Timeouts must be configured for all external service calls.
      - Set appropriate timeout values for service calls
      - Use different timeouts for different operations
      - Handle timeout errors gracefully
      - Document timeout values and rationale
      - Monitor timeout occurrences
    severity: error

  - id: service_integration.patterns.rate_limiting
    description: |
      Rate limiting must be implemented for external service calls.
      - Respect service rate limits
      - Implement client-side rate limiting when needed
      - Handle rate limit errors appropriately
      - Use exponential backoff on rate limit errors
      - Document rate limit policies
    severity: error

  - id: service_integration.patterns.validation
    description: |
      Service inputs and outputs must be validated.
      - Validate inputs before sending to external services
      - Validate outputs from external services
      - Use Pydantic models for request/response validation
      - Handle validation errors appropriately
      - Document validation requirements
    severity: error

  - id: service_integration.patterns.circuit_breaker
    description: |
      Circuit breaker pattern should be used for unreliable services.
      - Implement circuit breaker for services with high failure rates
      - Open circuit after threshold failures
      - Provide fallback behavior when circuit is open
      - Monitor circuit breaker state
      - Document circuit breaker configuration
    severity: warning

  - id: service_integration.patterns.service_discovery
    description: |
      Service discovery should be used for dynamic service locations.
      - Support service discovery mechanisms when needed
      - Handle service endpoint changes gracefully
      - Document service discovery configuration
      - Test service discovery behavior
    severity: warning

  - id: service_integration.patterns.health_checks
    description: |
      Service health checks must be implemented.
      - Check service availability before use
      - Implement health check endpoints for services
      - Monitor service health status
      - Handle unhealthy service states appropriately
      - Document health check procedures
    severity: warning

  - id: service_integration.patterns.versioning
    description: |
      Service versioning must be handled appropriately.
      - Support service API versioning
      - Handle service API changes and deprecations
      - Document service version requirements
      - Test with different service versions when applicable
    severity: warning

  - id: service_integration.patterns.security
    description: |
      Service integrations must be secure.
      - Use secure authentication mechanisms (API keys, OAuth, etc.)
      - Encrypt sensitive data in transit (HTTPS/TLS)
      - Validate service certificates
      - Never log or expose service credentials
      - Rotate service credentials regularly
    severity: error

  - id: service_integration.patterns.monitoring
    description: |
      Service integrations must be monitored.
      - Track service call metrics (latency, success rate, error rate)
      - Monitor service availability and health
      - Alert on service failures and degradations
      - Track service usage and costs
      - Document monitoring and alerting setup
    severity: warning

  - id: service_integration.quality.testing
    description: |
      Service integrations must be thoroughly tested.
      - Test service integration with mocks
      - Test error handling and retry logic
      - Test timeout and rate limiting behavior
      - Test with service simulators when available
      - Document testing procedures
    severity: error

examples:
  - description: "Service integration with retry and error handling"
    language: python
    code: |
      import time
      import requests
      from typing import Dict, Any, Optional
      from mavaia_core.exceptions import MavaiaError
      
      
      class ServiceIntegrationError(MavaiaError):
          """Base exception for service integration errors"""
          pass
      
      
      class ExternalServiceClient:
          """Client for external service with retry and error handling"""
          
          def __init__(
              self,
              base_url: str,
              api_key: str,
              timeout: int = 30,
              max_retries: int = 3,
              retry_delay: float = 1.0
          ):
              self.base_url = base_url
              self.api_key = api_key
              self.timeout = timeout
              self.max_retries = max_retries
              self.retry_delay = retry_delay
          
          def call_service(
              self,
              endpoint: str,
              params: Dict[str, Any]
          ) -> Dict[str, Any]:
              """Call external service with retry logic"""
              url = f"{self.base_url}/{endpoint}"
              headers = {"Authorization": f"Bearer {self.api_key}"}
              
              last_error = None
              for attempt in range(self.max_retries):
                  try:
                      response = requests.get(
                          url,
                          params=params,
                          headers=headers,
                          timeout=self.timeout
                      )
                      response.raise_for_status()
                      return {"success": True, "data": response.json()}
                  
                  except requests.exceptions.Timeout:
                      last_error = "timeout"
                      if attempt < self.max_retries - 1:
                          time.sleep(self.retry_delay * (2 ** attempt))  # Exponential backoff
                          continue
                  
                  except requests.exceptions.HTTPError as e:
                      if e.response.status_code in (429, 503, 502):  # Retryable errors
                          last_error = f"http_error_{e.response.status_code}"
                          if attempt < self.max_retries - 1:
                              time.sleep(self.retry_delay * (2 ** attempt))
                              continue
                      else:
                          # Non-retryable error
                          return {
                              "success": False,
                              "error": f"HTTP {e.response.status_code}: {str(e)}",
                              "error_code": "http_error"
                          }
                  
                  except Exception as e:
                      return {
                          "success": False,
                          "error": str(e),
                          "error_code": "unknown_error"
                      }
              
              # All retries exhausted
              return {
                  "success": False,
                  "error": f"Service call failed after {self.max_retries} attempts: {last_error}",
                  "error_code": "max_retries_exceeded"
              }

  - description: "Service with circuit breaker pattern"
    language: python
    code: |
      from enum import Enum
      from datetime import datetime, timedelta
      from typing import Dict, Any
      
      
      class CircuitState(Enum):
          CLOSED = "closed"
          OPEN = "open"
          HALF_OPEN = "half_open"
      
      
      class CircuitBreaker:
          """Circuit breaker for service calls"""
          
          def __init__(
              self,
              failure_threshold: int = 5,
              timeout_seconds: int = 60,
              half_open_timeout: int = 30
          ):
              self.failure_threshold = failure_threshold
              self.timeout_seconds = timeout_seconds
              self.half_open_timeout = half_open_timeout
              self.state = CircuitState.CLOSED
              self.failure_count = 0
              self.last_failure_time: Optional[datetime] = None
              self.last_success_time: Optional[datetime] = None
          
          def call(self, func, *args, **kwargs) -> Dict[str, Any]:
              """Execute function with circuit breaker protection"""
              if self.state == CircuitState.OPEN:
                  if self._should_attempt_reset():
                      self.state = CircuitState.HALF_OPEN
                  else:
                      return {
                          "success": False,
                          "error": "Circuit breaker is OPEN",
                          "error_code": "circuit_open"
                      }
              
              try:
                  result = func(*args, **kwargs)
                  self._on_success()
                  return result
              except Exception as e:
                  self._on_failure()
                  raise
          
          def _on_success(self):
              """Handle successful call"""
              self.failure_count = 0
              self.last_success_time = datetime.now()
              if self.state == CircuitState.HALF_OPEN:
                  self.state = CircuitState.CLOSED
          
          def _on_failure(self):
              """Handle failed call"""
              self.failure_count += 1
              self.last_failure_time = datetime.now()
              
              if self.failure_count >= self.failure_threshold:
                  self.state = CircuitState.OPEN
          
          def _should_attempt_reset(self) -> bool:
              """Check if circuit should attempt reset"""
              if self.last_failure_time:
                  time_since_failure = datetime.now() - self.last_failure_time
                  return time_since_failure.total_seconds() >= self.timeout_seconds
              return True

references:
  - Retry patterns: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/architecture/patterns/retry
  - Circuit breaker pattern: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/architecture/patterns/circuit-breaker
  - Mavaia service implementations: mavaia_core/services/
  - Web fetch service: mavaia_core/services/web_fetch_service.py
  - Tool registry: mavaia_core/services/tool_registry.py
